attachments.text:
Best for shirts is poly mailers-- cheap, light, and strong. Seems to be industry standard.

Best option for playmats I think is corrugated mailers. Avoids surcharges from shipping an irregular shape and avoids pissed-off recipients who are wieners about folded playmats. I'm getting them anywhere in the lower 48 for about $4.33 I think. 15x2x2 works well. They require special 2x7.5" shipping labels, though.
